    <article id="Lec27">
        <header class="html-article-header">
            <h2><span class="html-lec-heading">Lecture 27: List elements</span></h2>
        </header>
        <p class="sec-para-main">There are two types of lists- ordered <code class="html-tags">&ltol></code> and
            unordered<code class="html-tags">&ltul></code>. Unordered lists place it's list elements<code
                class="html-tags">&ltli></code> in bullet
            points while ordered lists store their elements in a numerical order. It is also possible to nest
            lists
            inside one another or other elements inside the lists.</p>
    </article>
    <article id="Lec28">
