        </header>
        <p class="sec-para-main">Anchor tags <code class="html-tags">&lta></code> is used to link to a
            webpage,file,
            or some location
            on the same page.It contains an href attribute which contains the link location. Attribute is
            information which we can pass in an element tag. We use "http://www" before a website address for an
            external/internet link to indicate that we are using HTTP protocol and not file protocol.
            <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/a">MDN for <code
                    class="html-tags">&lta></code> tag</a>
        </p>
    </article>
